    <p style="font-size:140% ">According to the NIST the Cloud offers several services of essential characteristics
      in particular the elasticity of the resources offered by cloud services, their simplicity
      access via the network, the pooling of resources, the increased agility of IS in the Cloud as well as
      that usage-based billing for cloud services:
      
</p>
  <section>
    <div class="card">
   <center>  <img src="n1.jpg" alt="portrait1"></center> 
      <div class="content">
        <h2 style="color: blue ; text-decoration: underline;">Resource Elasticity:</h2>
        
        <center>  <p1>In the cloud, new capacities can be automatically made available
          users in the event of an increase in demand. Conversely, they can be
          quickly put to sleep when no longer needed.
          This elasticity of Cloud services creates for the end user the illusion of a capacity
          infinite which can be put into service at any time.
          For corporate clients, this elasticity characteristic makes it possible, for example, to
          cope with peaks of activity that the internal infrastructure could not have absorbed, but also
          to consider new applications, for example supercomputing applications
          requiring several hundred machines for only a few hours,
          applications that the cost of an internal infrastructure would have made impossible without the
          Cloud. According to Bernard Ourghanlian, Microsoft's technical and security director, at
          About the Cloud “Virtually, the power is infinite”
          
          
        </p1></center>
       
      </div>
   
    </div>

    <div class="card">
    <center> <img src="n2.jpg" alt="portrait2"></center> 
      <div class="content">
        <h2 style="color: blue ; text-decoration: underline;">Simple access via the network:</h2>
       
        <center>    <p1>Cloud-type services are accessible through the network, whether it is the
          company LAN network for internal Cloud, internal access, Internet access
          or an IP leased line (or VPN access) for an external Cloud. This access takes place
          by means of standard mechanisms and protocols which notably allow the use
          Cloud services from multiple types of terminals.
            . 
        </p1></center> 
        
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
     <center><img src="n3.jpg" alt="portrait3"></center> 
      <div class="content">
        <h2 style="color: blue ; text-decoration: underline;">Controlled costs thanks to the pooling of resources and the effects
          of scales:</h2>
      
        <center>  <p1>Cloud resources are pooled and pooled to serve multiple
          users (several departments or divisions as part of an internal Cloud at
          company or several companies in the case of a public cloud service).
          Pooling can take place at multiple levels, whether in terms of resources
          physical (servers, storage, network, application server ......)
          Thanks to this pooling of resources, they are reallocated
          dynamic according to demand and SLAs (service level agreement) without
          the user does not have to perform any operation whatsoever. Each user is thus
          assured of the achievement of the performance objectives defined in the context of his contract
          
          

        </p1></center>
        
      </div>
    </div>
